{"GO":[{"def":"To move upon the feet, or step by step; to walk; also, to walk step by step, or leisurely.","pos":""}],"GO-BETWEEN":[{"def":"An intermediate agent; a broker; a procurer; -- usually in a disparaging sense.","pos":""}],"GO-BY":[{"def":"A passing without notice; intentional neglect; thrusting away; a shifting off; adieu; as, to give a proposal the go-by.","pos":""}],"GO-OUT":[{"def":"A sluice in embankments against the sea, for letting out the land waters, when the tide is out.","pos":""}]}